GLOBAL FIX: To prevent this class of bug, a structural change should be implemented. One approach is to set the pointer to `NULL` immediately after freeing it. This way, any subsequent calls to `free` will have no effect, as freeing a `NULL` pointer is a no-op in C. Additionally, implementing a memory management wrapper that tracks allocations and deallocations can help prevent double-free and other memory-related errors by ensuring that each allocation is matched with exactly one deallocation.

